15. whois command gives domain name, registry name, registration date etc about a website bought.
E.g. $ whois trainwithshubham.com, $ whois google.com (if required sudo apt install whois)

Some more commands:
1. route - Displays or modifies the system’s IP routing table (used to control network traffic paths).
E.g. $ route
Gives route table, also explore in AWS go to VPC and check route tables

2. nmap - command is network map like route table.
E.g. $ nmap -v trainwithshubham.com
command is used if no port is closed/open for hacking

